notes: All sequencing libraries were prepared from DNA of a single female  of the inbred line of red jungle fowl (UCD 001) to minimize  heterozygosity and provide sequence for both the Z and W sex  chromosomes, albeit at 50% of the autosomal coverage. (Hillier et al. Sequence and comparative analysis of  the chicken genome provide unique  perspectives on vertebrate evolution. Nature. 2004. 432: 695-777). "mtDNA  was  extracted  from  white  Leghorn  chicken   liver  mitochondria  as  described  (Desjardins  et al.,  1985)   and  further  purified  by  centrifugation  through  a  S-step   CsCl/ethidium  bromide  gradient  (Storrie  &  Attardi,  1972).   Japanese  quail,  Guinea  fowl,  pheasant  and  turkey   mtDNAs  were  isolated  according  to  the  same  procedure." (Desjardins and Morais. Sequence and Gene Organization of the  Chicken Mitochondrial Genome. J. Mol. Biol. (1999) 212: 599-634
